## Analysis

The missed optimization is transforming:
```llvm
%o = select i1 %y, i1 true, i1 %c    ; logical OR: %c | %y
%a = select i1 %c, i1 %x, i1 false   ; logical AND: %c & %x
%r = xor i1 %o, %a
```

Into:
```llvm
%1 = xor i1 %x, true
%r = select i1 %c, i1 %1, i1 %y
```

This matches the pattern `(A | B) ^ (A & C) -> A ? ~C : B`.

The current code handles `(A & B) ^ (A | C)` but needs to also handle the commuted case where the OR comes first: `(A | B) ^ (A & C)`.

## Proposed Patch

I need to add another pattern matching block that handles the case where Op0 is a logical OR and Op1 is a logical AND. This is symmetric to the existing pattern.

## Verification

For the test case:
- Op0 = `select i1 %y, i1 true, i1 %c` (logical OR: `%c | %y`)
- Op1 = `select i1 %c, i1 %x, i1 false` (logical AND: `%c & %x`)

With the new pattern `(A | B) ^ (C & D)`:
- A = %c, B = %y (from OR)
- C = %c, D = %x (from AND)
- A == C, so we get: `select i1 %c, i1 (not %x), i1 %y`

This matches the expected output.

